The mixture of flavours in this quiche is perfect and easy to make for busy people. Bacon, Gorgonzola, spinach, caramelised onions.  1 roll of puff pastry 1 large red onion finely chopped 1 tbsp sugar 2 cups finely chopped spinach 200g Georgies bacon bits 100g Gorgonzola cheese 4 eggs ¾ cup full cream milk ½ cup sour cream ¼ cup parsley finely chopped ½ cup Cheddar cheese grated 4 tbs butter   Method  Heat oven to 2000C. Use the butter to grease a large cupcake baking tray. Line the baking tray with pastry. Use a fork to prick the bottom of the crust. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.  Place 2 tablespoons of butter into a frying pan, add onion and sugar, fry until onions are cooked and caramelised. Allow to cool. Wilt the spinach in hot water, drain off excess water. In a large mixing bowl, whisk together egg, milk, sour cream. Add bacon, spinach, caramelised onion and Gorgonzola. Pour mixture into pastry cups. Bake for 25 minutes.  Serve hot with salad. The Saturday Star